document: Toulouse is a municipality in south-west France. With 486,828 inhabitants as of 1 January 2018, Toulouse is the fourth most populous commune in France after Paris, Marseille and Lyon, having gained 101,000 inhabitants over the last 47 years (1968-2015)
Montreal is the main city of Quebec. A large island metropolis and port on the St. Laurent River at the foot of the Lachine Rapids, it is the second most populous city in Canada, after Toronto.
Bordeaux is a French commune located in the Gironde department in the Nouvelle-Aquitaine region.
